    <title type="html"><![CDATA[PCLN Revisited]]></title>
    <link href="http://www.thetatrades.com/blog/2017/02/15/pcln-revisited/"/>
    <updated>2017-02-15T19:07:36-08:00</updated>
    <id>http://www.thetatrades.com/blog/2017/02/15/pcln-revisited</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>Hey traders,</p>

<p>We&rsquo;re currently looking at two potential bullish plays.</p>

<p>First is $PCLN:</p>

<p><a href="/images/blog/20170215/pcln.png"><img src="/images/blog/20170215/pcln.png" alt="$PCLN - 2017-02-15 - Daily" /></a></p>

<p>We had mentioned to get long <a href="/blog/2017/01/23/long-pcln/" title="Long PCLN">back on Jan 23</a>, and $PCLN has trended nicely since then. However, with the recent three day consolidation, and the bullishness of the market, $PCLN looks ready to break out higher for more upside gains. One can look to add more on a break above 1652.</p>

<p>Second is $TXN:</p>

<p><a href="/images/blog/20170215/txn.png"><img src="/images/blog/20170215/txn.png" alt="$TXN - 2017-02-15 - Daily" /></a></p>

<p>$TXN has also trended nicely over the past year, holding above the 50MA. We&rsquo;ve pulled back to it recently, making it a great location to get long. We&rsquo;re looking to get long above 75.76, with a stop at 72.20. We&rsquo;ll continue staying long as long as trend holds.</p>

